<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1885-04-02T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1885-04-02T00:00:00-05:00" n="67" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d67">
                    <opener><seg rendition="#center">No. 67.</seg></opener>
                    <head><hi rend="italic">Mr. <persName type="from">Hall</persName> to Mr.
                                <persName type="to">Bayard</persName></hi>.</head>
                    <opener><seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.]</seg></opener>
                    <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Legation of
                                    the United States in Central America</hi>,<lb/><hi rend="italic">Guatemala</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1885-04-02"><hi rend="italic">April</hi> 2, 1885</date>.
                            (Received April 16.)</dateline></opener>
                    <p>Mr. Hall informs the Department that a battle was fought to day (the 2d)
                        between the forces of Salvador and Guatemala, in which the President of
                        Guatemala was killed. He says the diplomatic corps has proposed an
                        armistice.</p>
                </div>
                </body></text></TEI>